## Writing Principles

1. **[PRINCIPLE 1 NAME]** — [What it means in practice. E.g., "Lead with what the user gets, not what they have to do."]
2. **[PRINCIPLE 2 NAME]** — [What it means. E.g., "First-person framing: 'You have $342 left' not 'Available balance: $342'"]
3. **[PRINCIPLE 3 NAME]** — [What it means. E.g., "Every word earns its place — if it doesn't add meaning, cut it."]
4. **[PRINCIPLE 4 NAME]** — [What it means. E.g., "Specificity over generality — 'Earn 2% back on groceries' not 'Earn rewards'"]
5. **[PRINCIPLE 5 NAME]** — [What it means. E.g., "Reduce anxiety, don't amplify it — status states should be informative, not alarming."]

