## Tone Arc

Tone shifts based on the user's situation. Define the arc here:

| Situation | Tone | Example |
|---|---|---|
| [Positive state — user is ahead/winning] | [Tone: warm, celebratory, confident] | "[Example string]" |
| [Neutral state — on track] | [Tone: calm, reassuring, clear] | "[Example string]" |
| [Warning state — needs attention] | [Tone: direct but not alarming] | "[Example string]" |
| [Negative state — shortfall, error, risk] | [Tone: urgent but actionable, never catastrophizing] | "[Example string]" |

