## Hard Rules (Non-Negotiable)

- **[RULE 1]** — [E.g., "No emdashes in any copy, ever. Use a comma, period, or rewrite the sentence."]
- **[RULE 2]** — [E.g., "Never use vague value terms without specificity: 'earn cashback' must name how much and from what."]
- **[RULE 3]** — [E.g., "Never use regulatory-sensitive language: 'loan', 'borrow', 'interest' on EWA features."]
- **[RULE 4]** — [E.g., "No passive voice in CTAs — 'Get started' not 'Get started now' (or worse, 'You can get started')."]
- **[RULE 5]** — [E.g., "No jargon the user didn't bring to the table."]

